  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the lamb shoulder and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the turnips, red wine, chicken broth, cumin, coriander, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, until the turnips are tender, about 30 minutes.",
    "Add the fresh cilantro and stir to combine.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional cilantro if desired.",
    "Dehydrate the stew in a low-temperature oven (150°F) for 1 hour to caramelize the turnips and thicken the sauce.",
    "Reheat the stew before serving.",
    "Serve with rice or crusty bread, if desired."
